edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.FinalProject

Class Save

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.csupomona.cs.cs141.FinalProject.Save
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Save
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This class will hold all of the objects and data that will need to be preserved if the data is saved in a single (serializable) object that can be saved and then read again later with the use of ObjectInputStream/ObjectOutputStream objects. This class will hold a single Map object (saving the state of the map and each of its individual Area objects), one Player object (to save the status of the player), and six Jedi objects (to keep track of the six Jedi enemies) so that the game can maintain the status of each of these objects by saving the data to a file which can be loaded at another time.
    Author:
    Team Jedi
